git
===

https://git-scm.com/download/win

https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Getting-Started-First-Time-Git-Setup

git --version (@ vscode)
https://github.com/loverence/angular-official.git

login into https://github.com/
Create repository
copy the url

@ vscode ==> file-> preferences -> settings -> search for "git enabled", that should be checked.
@ vscode ==> cntl+alt+p -> git clone -> set remote path and local path

*****
to clone git, from some source:
open terminal
go to the root folder - where your project folder is going to be created
git clone url
(ex: git clone https://github.com/DeborahK/Angular-RxJS.git)
*****

node -v
npm -v
npm install
npm audit fix
npm audit fix --force

npm install -g npm 

npm install -g @angular/cli
ng v

create folder
navigate to that folder

ng new my-app

*** SSL setup ***
at angular.json --> serve --> options --> add "ssl":true

      "serve": {
          "builder": "@angular-devkit/build-angular:dev-server",
          "options": {
            "browserTarget": "angular-official:build",
            "ssl": true
          },

****
typescript update

ng --version
tsc --version

npm install -g --save-dev typescript@latest

find the ts version number
open package.json => search "typescript" ==> change the version
run "npm install"

